description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Do you want to help us achieve our goal of delivering a first-class recruitment experience?An opportunity has arisen for an Apprentice Recruitment Administrator to join us during a time of great change. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust has just been awarded funding which will include some new buildings (HIP2 Project) and the Recruitment Team will be part of a new Resourcing Hub working collaboratively with our colleagues in Temporary Staffing and Voluntary Services, allowing us to deliver and develop our service even further.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We work to support managers and applicants through the whole recruitment process and you could be the person to help us do this.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Recruitment Team is often the first point of contact for applicants and new employees so part of your role will be to ensure that they receive a positive experience, with excellent customer service and a friendly approach&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work closely with the rest of the team in helping to provide an end to end recruitment process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key points of the role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Undertaking the required NHS pre-employment checks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring electronic records are updated and personal information recorded accurately&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting recruitment events including open days and jobs fairs. These are occasionally held at weekends and it essential that you can be flexible with your working hours when required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Arranging interviews for managers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Issuing offer letters and employment contracts ensuring information is accurate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is full time working 37.5 hours per week and may currently involve working from home.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Benefits of working at Torbay and South Devon NHS Foundation Trust include:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;27 days annual leave upon entry to the NHS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS Pension Scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS discounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunities to undertake training to enhance your CPD&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For more information, or an informal chat, please contact Ros Banfield, Recruitment Manager (ros.banfield@nhs.net).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look forward to hearing from you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
